description: Today has marked two weeks since my daughter walked away from a treatment faculty in Portland.  There has been a possible sighting, last Wednesday, in Newberg. I thank those of you who have been kind enough to share her photo to others I do not know.    Unfortunately, it has been disheartening with some close friends who have told me, “Oh, I will do that the minute I get home.” THEY DON”T!    Or, thos ... e who say, “I don’t have many friends.”  OKAY. COULD YOU SEND HER PHOTO TO THE FEW FRIENDS YOU APPARENTLY ONLY HAVE IN THIS WORLD???    Or, “I’m hardly ever on Facebook.”  COULD YOU POSSIBLY LOG ON ONE MORE TIME? MY DAUGHTER IS MISSING!    You should hear some of the suggestions for how I should deal with this.  They are suggestions such as, “Fill your mind with positive thoughts” and “When things get a little stressful, hold ice cubes in your hands.”  SERIOUSLY!!!    I cannot express how much I appreciate those of you who have said to me, “Rob, I wouldn’t know what to do if my daughter was missing,” and those of you who have told me “I don’t know what to say but, I will pray for you.”    Please continue to share my daughter’s photo.  She is a wonderful young lady who needs our love and prayers.    Hug those you love, send someone an email telling them how much they mean to you, and give thanks.   See More
